[G3.4 — stalk flatness over the local base via transitivity]
  \label{lem:gf_stalk_flat_localBase}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.gf_stalk_flat_localBase}
  \uses{lem:gf_stalk_flat_over_base, lem:mathlib_localization_flat, lem:mathlib_flat_trans}
  In the situation of \cref{lem:gf_flat_locality_assembly}, let \(x \in V = D(f)\) and
  let \(y \in p^{-1}(V)\) be a source point with \(p(y)\) a generization of \(x\).
  Then the stalk \(\F_y\) is flat over the local ring \(\OO_{S,x}\).
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:gf_stalk_flat_over_base, lem:mathlib_localization_flat, lem:mathlib_flat_trans}
  By \cref{lem:gf_stalk_flat_over_base}, \(\F_y\) is flat over \(\OO_{S,\,p(y)}\). As
  \(p(y)\) is a generization of \(x\), the comparison map
  \(\OO_{S,x} \to \OO_{S,\,p(y)}\) is a localization, hence \(\OO_{S,\,p(y)}\) is flat
  over \(\OO_{S,x}\) (\cref{lem:mathlib_localization_flat}). Transitivity of flatness
  along \(\OO_{S,x} \to \OO_{S,\,p(y)} \to \F_y\)
  (\cref{lem:mathlib_flat_trans}) upgrades ``\(\F_y\) flat over \(\OO_{S,\,p(y)}\)'' to
  ``\(\F_y\) flat over \(\OO_{S,x}\)''.
\end{proof}

